    "updated_at": "2014-12-09T04:00:18Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Looks good to me. What about Python's own `--user` prefix (`site.getuserbase()`)? An advantage of supporting sys.prefix is that kernelspec files can be provided with Python packages via data_files, but if one installs a wheel with a kernelspec with `--user`, it wouldn't be found.\n"
  },
