    "created_at": "2014-12-09T17:39:29Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-12-09T17:39:29Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'd like it to be possible to do per-user install with non-Python tools as well. Python's userbase location (ultimately coming from `sysconfig._getuserbase()`) is Python specific if:\n- The PYTHONUSERBASE environment variable is set\n- Running on Windows\n- Running on Mac where Python is a 'framework'\n\nSo, for the moment, I'm inclined to say that kernels distributed as Python packages can't be wheels.\n"
  },
