    "updated_at": "2014-12-09T18:53:11Z",
    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I'm not concerned about our code supporting installation into there, but I do think it makes sense to add it to the search path, since it seems a trivial addition to the list.\n\n> kernels distributed as Python packages can't be wheels.\n\nIt also means that kernels cannot be installed with Python packages via data_files at all, and setup.py must import and invoke IPython.\n"
